4. Termination
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
If the customer's &WEBSYSNAVN. agreement is terminated, the
registration agreement for the receipt of electronic payment
information is deemed to have been terminated.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The customer will then receive the list of payments in paper form
unless the customer's account with &BANKNAVN has been closed to
the effect that the entire registration agreement is deemed to
have been terminated.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
5. Errors, delays, etc.
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS8.
In the event of errors or delays in connection with electronic
payment information, and such errors or delays have been caused by
the banks involved or Nets, the banks or Nets must remedy the error
or reprovide the service if possible without financial
consequences that are disproportionate to the agreed service.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The bank is liable for direct losses inflicted on the customer due
to negligence on the part of the banks involved or Nets. This does
not apply where such losses are due to the customer's own affairs,
including defects in the customer's own equipment such as
computers, programmes and modem. Neither the bank nor Nets incurs
liability if losses are due to the affairs of a provider chosen by
the customer, such as a telecom company or an Internet provider.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
Neither the banks involved nor Nets are liable for indirect loss.
